<bdy>

<b>Gilbert R. Hill</b> (born 1931) is a former President of the <administrative_unit wordnetid="108077292" confidence="0.8">
<council wordnetid="108310949" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../748/15666748.xml">
Detroit City Council</link></council>
</administrative_unit>
.  He was also a Detroit police officer and part-time actor, gaining notoriety in the <movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../398/680398.xml">
Beverly Hills Cop</link></movie>
 movie franchise.<p>

Born in <village wordnetid="108672738" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../427/85427.xml">
Birmingham, Alabama</link></village>
, Hill is a former police detective in the City of Detroit. He also appeared in the <it><movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../398/680398.xml">
Beverly Hills Cop</link></movie>
</it> films, playing the role of Inspector Todd, opposite <comedian wordnetid="109940146" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<person wordnetid="100007846" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../539/54539.xml">
Eddie Murphy</link></person>
</comedian>
.<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%221%22])">1</ref>  Hill was elected to the Detroit City Council in 1989, and ran unsuccessfully for Mayor of Detroit against <person wordnetid="100007846" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<officeholder wordnetid="110371450" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../947/319947.xml">
Kwame Kilpatrick</link></officeholder>
</person>
 in the 2001 election.</p>

